column2: 2:17 PM) (There have been a lot of questions regarding this new term “potential tropical cyclone
column3: ” which assists with tropical interference.  New product helps track tropical cyclones'Potential tropical cyclones' numbered equally with depressions  This new product enables advisories
column4: watches and warnings for tropical disturbances that pose a threat for tropical storm or hurricane conditions to a land mass within 48 hours.  Starting this year
column5: these tropical systems are in advisory products and numbered equally with depressions. For example
column6: a Tropical Cyclone 3 can become Tropical Depression 3 or skip directly to a tropical storm if it’s the same system that has strengthened.  People in the areas that may be affected should start paying extra attention to the movement and strength of the system and have their personal preparations ready.  This new change makes it possible to get preparations underway earlier than waiting for the storm to fully form.) () () (Weather Blog: Despite recent rain

column18: 4:34 PM) (We are almost out of the dry season and heading toward the all-important wet season here in Florida.  Central Florida heading into wet weather seasonSeason last usually from late May to mid-October Location of Bermuda High can determine where storms will be   The season usually begins in late May and lasts through the middle part of October. The key players are the "Bermuda High
column19:
along with the high heat and humidity — the very things that make it somewhat uncomfortable outside during the summer but keep our landscaping green and thriving.  The Bermuda High is named for the region in which it usually stays for the summer months. It does wobble a bit, and that's where meteorology comes in.  Depending on its location, we can predict where the west and east coast sea breezes will meet and spark up heavy showers and storms. The high heat over the land causes the air to rise and be replaced by the sea breeze on both coasts.  If the prevailing winds are out of the east, then the collision will be over the western half of the peninsula. If they are south, the collision will be down the middle of the state. It is these days of 40 to 50 percent chance of showers and storms that amount to the majority of our annual rainfall.  So if your yard is brown and crunchy, don’t despair — the wet season is almost here, but it will take awhile to recover from the deficit we are in now. ) () () (Weather Blog: Several records set in April across Central Florida) (May 23, 4:14 PM) (April was yet another month with warmer and drier weather than normal. We now have a severe or moderate drought index across Central Florida. We set quite a few records. Let’s start with the records:  Orlando  April 3 had a record warm low of 71 degrees. The previous record was 69 degrees set in 1980.April 5 had a record high of 96 degrees. The previous record was 91 degrees set in 1999.   Melbourne  April 3 had a record warm low of 76 degrees. The previous record was 71 degrees set in 1960.April 4 tied a record warm low of 71 degrees set in 1974.April 5 had a record high of 92 degrees. The previous record was 91 degrees set in 1977.April 10 tied a record warm low of 71 degrees set in 1953.April 15 had a record warm low of 74 degrees. The previous record was 73 degrees set in 2015.April 16 had a record warm low of 73 degrees. The previous record was 72 degrees set in 2011.April 19 tied a record warm low of 74 degrees set in 1989.April 21 tied a record warm low of 73 degrees set in 2006.April 24 tied record high of 92 degrees set in 1963.April 28 had a record warm low of 76 degrees. The previous record was 74 degrees set in 2013.April 29 had a record warm low of 78 degrees, which was the all-time record warm low for the site in the month of April. The previous record was 74 degrees set in 2003.April 30 had a record warm low of 76 degrees. The previous record was 73 degrees set in 2012.   Daytona Beach  April 3 had a record warm low of 70 degrees. The previous record was 69 degrees set in 1929.April 5 had a record high of 91 degrees. The previous record was 90 degrees set in 1957.April 29 had a record warm low of 74 degrees. The previous record was 73 degrees set in 1991.April 30 had a record warm low of 75 degrees, which is the all-time record warm low for the site in the month of April. The previous record was 72 degrees set in 1991.Here are the average temperatures:Orlando had a monthly average temperature of 74.4 degrees, which was 3.2 degrees above normal. This ties 2006, 2002 and 1912 as the ninth warmest April on record for this site.Daytona Beach had a monthly average temperature of 71.9 degrees, which was 3.0 degrees above normal.Melbourne had a monthly average temperature of 76.0 degrees, which was 5.6 degrees above normal. This ranks as the second warmest April on record for this site.   April rainfall  Orlando had a trace of rain for the month, which was 2.68 inches below normal. This ranked as the second driest April on record for the site.Daytona Beach had 1.22 inches of rain for the month, which was 0.96 inches below normal.Melbourne had 0.23 inches of rain for the month, which was 1.90 inches below normal. This ranks as the fifth driest April on record for the site.Clermont had 0.30 inches of rain for the month, which ranks as the seventh driest April on record for the site.Sanford had 0.51 inches of rain for the month, which ranks as the sixth driest April on record for the site. ) () () (WEATHER BLOG: Central Florida saw warmer, drier March than normal) () () (Weather Blog: Saturn moon has active water, researchers say)

tenmb.asl.americansignlanguagepro () () () () () () () () (ASL History) () () () () (In the early 1800's
column2: Thomas Hopkins Gallaudet
column3: a hearing minister and a graduate of Yale University met and became friends with a young Deaf girl named Alice. Gallaudet took an interest in teaching the girl and succeeded at teaching her a few words. The girl's father Dr. Mason Cogswell
column4: encouraged Gallaudet to become involved with the establishment of a school for the Deaf.) (So
column5: in 1815 Gallaudet headed for Europe in search of methods for teaching the Deaf.He approached a number of program directors
column6: (the Braidwood schools
column7: the London Asylum
column8: etc.)
column9: but none of them were willing to share their techniques with Gallaudet.) (Fortunately while in England Gallaudet met up with the director of a Paris school for the Deaf
column10: a man by the name of Sicard.Sicard was there with two of his deaf pupils
column11: Jean Massieu and Laurent Clerc who were also teachers at the school in Paris. They were in England giving demonstrations on how to teach the deaf by using sign language. The Paris school
column12: which had been founded by the Abbe Charles Michel de L'Epee in 1771
column13: was using French Sign Language in combination with a set methodically developed signs.) (Gallaudet persuaded Clerc to return with him to the States and in 1817 the first American school for the deaf was established in the city of Hartford
column14: Connecticut. Over time
column15: the signs used at that school
column16: plus the signs that were already being used by Deaf people in America evolved into what we now know as American Sign Language.)

column3: 2017) () (Killian Dain & Alexander Wolfe def. Kassius Ohno & Hideo Itami) (ORLANDO
column4: Fla. — If Kassius Ohno and Hideo Itami’s friendship was on thin ice before
column5: you better believe that ice has completely cracked following their loss to Killian Dain & Alexander Wolfe.  Ohno and Itami’s inexperience as a tag team – and issues communicating – would ultimately be their undoing in this bout. At times
column6: Ohno could be heard imploring his tag team partner to tag him into the contest
column7: only to see his pleas going ignored by Itami.  On the other side of the squared circle
column8: SAniTy’s crazed team of Dain & Wolfe worked in complete unity. The unhinged Wolfe appeared to gladly take a GTS from Itami in order to open the door for The Beast of Belfast
column9: who then demolished Itami with a devastating running cross body .  With Ohno and Itami clearly not on the same page
column10: will this loss add fuel to the fire that is their tumultuous friendship?) () (NXT Champion Bobby Roode def. Roderick Strong) (In front of his family and the NXT Universe
column11: Roderick Strong put up a valiant effort
column12: but ultimately fell short in his effort to become NXT Champion.  Both challenger and champion took turns dishing out their own brand of calculated offense. Strong delivered high-impact backbreakers while NXT Champion Bobby Roode homed in on his opponent’s left leg. At one point
column13: after The Glorious One slammed Strong’s injured leg between the steel steps and the ring post moments prior
column14: the referee asked the challenger if he wished to continue. Strong was having no part of that idea
column15: and instead managed to will himself back into the contest and mount another innovative offensive attack.  As the rivals traded near falls
column16: the bout appeared to be over after the NXT Champion hit Strong with the Glorious DDT. Yet The Messiah of the Backbreaker again somehow mustered up enough strength to kick out
column17: and this epic title showdown continued.  With the champion positioned to hit another Glorious DDT
column18: he instead took time to taunt Strong’s family at ringside. This lit a fire under the embattled Strong
column19: who countered Roode with a kick to the face
column20: followed by a knee to the champion’s chin. Strong looked like he was launched out of a rocket as he continued his assault into a devastating backbreaker before seeming to pick up the victory.  The crowd at Full Sail University erupted in approval at the referee’s count of three. The ring announcer began to announce Strong as the new NXT Champion
column21: until he was cut off by the referee who explained that Roode’s foot was under the rope.  As Strong tried to come to grips with what just happened
column23: kicking his adversary to the floor right in front of his fiancé and mother. The NXT Champion then hit a Glorious DDT onto Strong outside the ring
column24: while Strong’s family watched in dismay.  Roode then threw Strong back in the ring and hit one more Glorious DDT to pick up the emotional victory
column25: and once again walk out of Full Sail University the NXT Champion.  After nearly claiming the NXT Title
column26: only to be defeated seconds later
column27: will Strong get another opportunity at the Roode’s glorious championship?)

column2: searching for decorations for her new house
column3: when inspiration struck. She promptly went home and pulled out her collection of photo albums
column4: from which she selected five pictures to be cropped
column5: enlarged
column6: framed
column7: and hung on her walls. Each photograph marks a different special event in Dorothea's life (including her engagement) and shows Dorothea posing with a different person (one of whom is a favorite cousin). Each of the five photographs has a different backdrop (one was taken at a fancy restaurant)
column8: but Dorothea has no trouble remembering the event connected with each one
column9: as she received a different treasured gift (including a set of engraved candlesticks) to mark each occasion. From the following clues
column10: can you match the person with the backdrop and event shown in each of the photographs
column11: as well as with the gift each gave to Dorothea?) () () () () (Puzzle 2) () (Seconds
column12: Anyone? ) (by Evelyn Jones) (Ian loves concocting new recipes
column14: over the course of the two weeks after his move to his new apartment
column15: he had a number of people over to sample his experiments! Each person (including Morgan)
column16: each of whom is a different relation to Ian (one person is his boss)
column17: was served a different food (including avocado-stuffed apples) and came by on a different day during the first two weeks. From the following clues
column18: can you determine the order in which each guest visited Ian
column19: his or her relationship to Ian
column20: and the dish that he or she sampled? Note: Each name could apply to a man or a woman.) () () () () (Puzzle 3) () (Cat Nap ) (by J. Bethel Brown) (Mr. Langersham often comes home from work in the afternoons to find his five cats sleeping. Recently
column21: he discovered each feline (including Grizelda) napping in a different location in the house. He has owned each cat for a different number of years (from one through five)
column22: and each is a different age (three
column23: four
column24: five
column25: six
column26: or eight years old). Of course
column27: Mr. Langersham hasn't owned any of his pets for more years than its own age. Can you match each cat with the location in which it was sleeping
column28: its age
column29: and the number of years for which it has been with Mr. Langersham?) () () () () (Puzzle 4) () (All That Jazz ) (by Charles R. com.dailyroads.v () () (Visibility options) () () () () () (Our long-term goal is to build, organize and make accessible the largest free database of videos recorded on the roads around the globe. We need your help to achieve this, so please upload to DailyRoads.com only geotagged videos with their visibility set to public or anonymous. Please obey local privacy laws when uploading such videos.    - Public: everybody can view the video with the GPS route, listen to its sound track, and see your username.   - Anonymous: everybody can view the video and its GPS route, but sound is disabled, and the username is hidden.   - Friends: same as the public option, but only your friends can view the video. The list of friends can be managed on the site.   - Private: only you can have access to the video.   Only a limited number of private and friends videos/photos are allowed for each user. When the limit is reached, no new files are accepted. The current limits can be viewed here: http://dailyroads.com/voyager/m/upload_limits   Until the long-overdue redesign of the site is finalized, the anonymous visibility is treated as private, but without enforcing the limits.) Press the MENU button or swipe up for more options, such as changing playing strength. Long-press anywhere in the notation window to export the game as PGN or FEN to the clipboard, to set up a position, or to save and load the game as a file.   The application complies with the official chess rules, including en-passant, castling, and minor promotion. It recognizes a draw by stalemate, the fifty move rule, threefold repetition, and insufficient material.   The GUI supports the UCI and XBoard protocols. column1: rubicoin.rubicoinlearn () () () () () () () (Why Buy Stocks?) () () () () () () () () (Why Buy Stocks?) (The Nutshell  •  Owning stock means owning a piece of a company.  •  Invested funds are working for you 24/7.  •  Invested money can grow much faster than cash in a savings account.  Ever wanted to own part of a great business? That’s exactly what happens when you purchase stock. You’re buying a part of that company. As a part owner
column2: you’re entitled to a share of the profits and assets of that business.   You profit from owning stock in one of two ways.   1)The company can decide to return money to their shareholders via dividends. This is cash that is paid to you on a regular basis for being a shareholder.   2)The business grows and the price per share increases. Once you decide to sell your shares
column3: you pocket the returns.   While money kept in a savings account gets eaten away by inflation
column4: invested money is working for you 24/7. Unlike a bank account
column5: your original outlay can multiply many times over if you invest in the right companies.   On average
column6: the stock market has returned around 10% annually since 1974 (without factoring in inflation). That easily beats the 0.5% you’ll get by keeping your money in a savings account. ) ()

column8: there will be a icon heart icon with + symbol(Add to favorites). When you click that icon that present picture will be added to your Favorites section.  How to remove pictures from Favorites?  Goto the image that you want to remove from Favorites
column9: there will be a icon with only heart symbol(means already in Favorites list). When you click on that icon there will be popup asking whether you wanto remove from Favorites or not? Once you confirm that present picture will be removed from Favorites section.  Why Favorites section and what you can do with this?  Favorites option is useful to mark pictures that you like very much(beautiful or attractive) to Favorites section. Once you added to Favorites then you can see only those pictures that you like instead of all gallery pictures. You can play slideshow also with favorites by pressing Slideshow option from menu section.  )

co.easy4u.writer () () () () () () () (Welcome to Writer Plus) () () () () () () () () () (# Writer Plus Welcome to Writer Plus! This file will guide you through some of Writer Plus's features
column2: and give you an introduction to the philosophy behind it.  ## Why did I develop the app? James McMinn's Writer is one of my favorite writing tools
column3: but it is buggy and hasn't been upgraded for 4 years. So I decided to develop an enhanced app following it's philosophy
column4: and to keep on improving it according to users' reviews.  ## What is the "philosophy" that I mean? KEEP IT SIMPLE: That is the idea and philosophy behind Writer Plus. Writing should not be about the tools that you use
column5: but about the ideas and thoughts that you have. Writer Plus aims to give you a simple and enjoyable method to pour your ideas into a text.  ## What are the new features?   - Android Material Design   - Folder (Long press the "+" button)   - Undo & Redo   - Style: Font
column6: Night Mode   - Share   - And many more...  ## Where are my files located? Files are stored in sdcard://Writer/. The documents can be backed up or synced with your Google Drive account
column7: with [Writer Sync](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=co.easy4u.writer.sync).  ## Give it some character Sometimes plain text just doesn't feels right. Writer Plus supports basic [Markdown](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown). That means that you can add *emphasis* or **make a bold statement** in such a simple way.  *A full list of supported markdowns are listed at the end of this document.*  # Happy Writing If you enjoy using Writer Plus
column8: have a request
column9: found a bug
column10: or simply want to contact the developer
column11: then I'd love to hear it from you. Feel free to contact me via email: support@writer.plus.  If you have found it useful
column12: then please give it a high rating on the Android market. :D  # Markdown  # Header 1 ## Header 2 ### Header 3 You can do ~~Scratch~~
column14: **bold** or even ***both***!   + Writer does lists too!   + Weee!   - They can start with a + or a -   - I like the dashes more.  1. Numbered lists too!  2. Lots of lists   > Writer also supports quotes.   > But don't quote me on that. )

column1: com.omniluxtrade.veganrecipes () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () (Fishdom: Deep Dive) () () () (Looking for your cool new app? Download me now.) (Sponsored) (Install) () (Ingredients) () () () (4 carrots (cut into bun lengths)) (¼ cup seasoned rice vinegar (or apple cider vinegar and a dash of salt)) (¼ cup water) (1 tablespoon sesame oil) (2 tablespoons coconut aminos (can sub soy sauce but use unseasoned vinegar)) (¼ teaspoon garlic powder (or ½ clove garlic minced)) ( dash a dash or two liquid smoke) ( pepper to taste) () () (Add to shopping list) (Clear) () () () (Instruction) () (Fill a pot about half-way full of water
column2: heat it on high until it boils. Turn down to medium heat and add the carrots. Cook until you can just pierce it through with a fork. You want it to still have a snap when you eat it. Run cold water over them to stop them from cooking more. Combine the other ingredients to make the marinade. Use a container that has a tight lid so you can easily shake it without spraying it all over your kitchen. Marinate at least 3 to 4 hours
column3: though they are fine for almost 2 days. Put the carrots in the container and marinade for a few hours to up to a few days. If you marinate them longer they take on more of the vinegar flavor. If the carrots are very skinny I would not marinade them for more than 1 1/2 days so they don’t taste too sour. To serve heat the carrots in a 350 degree oven or on in a grill pan on a hot grill until heated through. It should take about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve in a toasted hot dog bun with your favorite toppings. They’re great the southern way topped with chili and cole slaw! Prep these on a weekend and you’re ready for a quick weeknight treat.) ()

column2: as well as the difference between a queen-sized bed and a king-sized bed. Not even furniture store attendants are well aware of the differences.) (     The size of your bed
column3: however
column4: is crucial to the quality of sleep that you will be getting. So
column5: it is important for you to get the bed size that is just perfect for you as well as for your partner if you are not sleeping alone.) (Here is a rough guide to bed sizes.) (     Singles - Single beds are also known as twin beds or bunk beds. They are often placed for use in children's rooms
column6: in multiple use guestrooms and in dorm rooms. A typical single bed is 39 inches wide and 75 inches long; it is ideal for small bedrooms.) (     The great thing about single beds is that you will not find it difficult to find sheets for them
column7: because sheets for single beds are the ones most available in furniture and department stores. Single beds are also usually fitted with trundle beds that you can pull out if you have a guest sleeping over.) (     The problem with single beds
column8: however
column9: is that they are mostly too short to accommodate adults. If you really want a single bed but you feel that it would be too short for you
column10: you can opt to buy an extra long single bed

column1: x.abcd () () () () () () () () (Overwhelm your victim  The “Application flooder” although technically harmless
column2: is a really annoying virus. Now that we’re moving further along in making batch file viruses
column3: let’s stop for a second to discuss a couple of basic commands:  @echo off – This command stops the batch file from showing the commands as they are being carried out
column4: that is the command window will not show the commands as they are being performed. However
column5: the output or error of the commands on execution will still be printed out in the command prompt window which is exactly like the cmd.exe window. We use this command when we don’t want to notify the user that something is going on
column6: to hide unnecessary background details so that the user can’t actually see what’s causing trouble – which is what we’re doing here. Note that the command window will still show up
column7: but there are methods to get around even this (to which we’ll get to later on).  // – The ‘//’ (- two slashes) is used in A LOT of places to insert comments. A comment is just some text (or string)
column8: usually inserted to give the program’s reader some help in understanding the code. Whenever any compiler or say the command line interpreter bumps into // – It ignores everything that comes after it
column9: in that line. It just skips it over
column10: pretends there’s nothing there
column11: and moves on to the next line. In many programming languages too
column12: like C
column14: Java etc. you will find comments exactly like these everywhere.  Getting to the interesting bit
column15: below we have the code for the application flooder virus. As always you can type it in a notepad and save as a .bat file (any name). Try to understand what’s going on below and then head over to the explanation.  @echo off ￼ //label start winword //MS word start mspaint //paint start notepad start write //wordpad start cmd //cmd prompt start explorer start control //panel start calc //calculator goto x //infinite loop  Explanation: So
column16: we start off by turning off “echo”. Now
column17: the user won’t know which file is running and what’s causing havoc on their innocent computer. We set a label
column18: say x. Now “start” is used to
column20: start applications. We can start these application by using the names of their executable files (the ones that runs these applications). So
column21: the user will see – Paint
column23: Control Panel
column24: NotePad
column25: WordPad etc. – All of them opening up for seemingly no reason. Check out the last line
column26: “goto x”
column27: remember that label we set up top named ‘x’? The goto statement send the program back to the beginning causing an infinite loop (that will probably run several times a second). So
column28: the victim’s computer will be drowned in a sea of random applications coming out of nowhere
column29: and opening up faster than he can close them. It will eat up all the RAM
column30: making the computer lag and possibly restart or making the user push the power button. Nevertheless kids
column31: don’t try this at home.  Even though today our systems can handle a lot of stuff all at once
column32: there’s still some minor risk in this batch file causing the windows to crash
column33: maybe leave permanent damage too.  )

column1: tarot.fortuneteller.reading () () () () () (How to ask a question?) () () (Tarot only works for those who are willing to listen. These are a few guidelines that are worth following:) (You should either ask a question or make a request. Both are valid. Saying 'What does the future hold for me?' and 'Tell me about my future' are the same to the Tarot. Also
column2: avoid giving the Tarot reader unnecessary details.) (Avoid questions that have a yes/no answer. It is a limiting question because there are only two possible answers: yes
column3: or no.) (Avoid questions starting in the 'Will I…'format... For example
column4: it is best not to ask questions like 'Will I get a raise?' or 'Will I get married?' As the answers to these questions depend entirely on you.) (Keep your options open. And avoid asking close-ended questions that have limited answers. Also try not to bring in a time-element in your questions.) (Asking a question is not as accurate as making a request. The request format eliminates preconceived notions about the outcome of the reading
column5: and results in a reading that is more insightful and helpful.) () (Close)

com.samapoh.carfaultdiagnosis () () () () () () () () (Car Fault Diagnosis) () () () () (5 Warning Lights You Should Never Ignore) () () (If any of the below warning lights come on while you are driving
column2: DO NOT IGNORE THEM! Immediate action may be necessary to prevent damage to your vehicle
column3: a breakdown or an accident.) (OIL PRESSURE WARNING LIGHT) () (The oil pressure warning light comes on if your engine has lost oil pressure or oil pressure is too low for safe engine operation. You should pull over to the side of the road
column4: shut the engine off and check the oil level on the engine dipstick.  Possible Causes: Low oil level (due to oil consumption or leaks)
column5: oil viscosity too thin
column6: worn oil pump
column7: excessive engine bearing clearances or defective oil pressure sending unit.  If you engine is also making ticking
column8: clattering or rapping noises
column9: it is not getting sufficient oil. If you attempt to drive the engine in this condition
column10: you will probably damage it - if it hasn't already suffered major internal damage.) (TEMPERATURE WARNING LIGHT) () (The temperature warning light will come on if your engine is overheating. Do NOT continue driving if your engine is overheating as this can cause expensive engine damage (piston scuffing
column11: valve stem galling
column12: failed head gasket
column13: cracks or distortion in cylinder head). Stop driving
column14: pull over and shut your engine off. Open the hood and check the radiator and heater hoses
column15: radiator and engine for coolant leaks. Note the level of the coolant in the coolant reservoir.  CAUTION: DO NOT open the coolant reservoir or radiator cap until the engine has cooled off for at least 30 minutes. Steam pressure inside the cooling system can blow out and burn you!  If the coolant level is low
column16: add coolant (a 50/50 mixture of antifreeze and clean distilled water) after the engine has cooled down.  Possible Causes: Low coolant level (due to coolant leak or bad head gasket)
column17: stuck thermostat
column18: bad water pump
column21: clogged or dirty radiator
column22: exhaust restriction (plugged catalytic converter).  HINT: Turning the A/C OFF and turning the heater on HIGH may help cool down an engine that is temporarily overheating due to unusually hot weather or from towing a trailer. But if the engine is running hot because it is low on coolant
column23: this trick probably won't help much.)

column26: Houghton Mifflin Harcourt
column27: 2003).     # # #    The Power of Food   For Marcus Samuelsson
column28: food tells a story. It speaks to a time and place
column29: reflecting the soul of a community.    He sees this in Harlem
column30: an African-American enclave in the New York borough of Manhattan that rose to prominence in the '20s and later fell on economic hardship.    “I’ve always been intrigued by it
column31: ” Samuelsson says of Harlem. “But I had to ask myself
column32: what can I add to this landscape
column33: and do I have anything to say?”  Samuelsson
column34: a native of Ethiopia who was adopted and raised in Sweden
column35: arrived in New York to apprentice at Aquavit
column36: a contemporary Swedish restaurant. In short order
column37: he earned the top job
column38: and at 24 became the youngest executive chef to garner a three-star review from the New York Times.  He appreciated the Aquavit clientele and the restaurant’s well-heeled Midtown surroundings. But none of it resonated in a truly meaningful way.   The desire to connect and to be a part of something bigger than himself drew him to Harlem. After work
column39: Samuelsson would head uptown to eat (Sylvia’s is a favorite)
column40: check out the nightclubs
column41: listen to jazz and be a part of the community that gave rise to the Harlem Renaissance. This intellectual and cultural movement of African-American writers
column43: artists and musicians flourished in the '20s through the mid-'30s
column44: producing some of the world’s greatest writers
column45: from Langston Hughes to W.E.B. DuBois.   Samuelsson made Harlem his home 15 years ago but it took seven of them to answer his question of whether he could contribute to the culinary landscape. He needed to wrap his head around the Harlem inspired by the past but largely ignored by the present.   In 2010 Samuelsson opened Red Rooster Harlem
column46: telling his story though American comfort food with nods to his Swedish and African roots. Two years later
column47: he started Ginny’s Supper Club downstairs from The Rooster as a musical and culinary tribute to the Harlem Renaissance. In 2015 he opened Streetbird Rotisserie
column48: a casual spot for rotisserie-style chicken and several other favorites such as mac ‘n cheese and fried chicken.  “I’ve always worked globally
column49: ” he says. “But I am also inspired by what’s around me. We cook food that speaks to the neighborhood.”  That food includes dishes like Helga’s meatballs
column50: a specialty of his grandmother's who instilled in him a love for cooking
column51: fried green tomatoes and shrimp and grits.  Samuelsson’s efforts to restore the community through food cast the local and national spotlight on Harlem. Other restaurants opened along with retailers
column52: bringing jobs but also gentrification.   In 2015
column54: an annual four-day celebration of food
column55: culture and the spirit of the community. Local eateries are given the opportunity showcase their food
column56: some of which is made by the country's most prominent culinary talents.   “We do food that shows what it means be a part of restoring a community
column57: ” Samuelsson says. “Every one has a story to tell.”) () () () () () () () () () (Recipes) () () () () () () () () () () () (Folio) () () () () ()

column2: the app collects Call/SMS/location information of the device in the background even when the app is not in foreground or opened. This information is collected periodically and user can view their Call/SMS/location information by using the app. You can choose to disable the collection of Call/SMS/location information by using the check box in the main view of the app. These information will *not* be published over internet unless you request for it from our server. The information will be stored securely in your mobile  WORKING OF THE APPLICATION  The app works as follows  1. Every time you receive a call/SMS or make a call or send SMS
column3: the location information of the mobile is fetched. 2. All the Call/SMS/location visited along with the time will be shown by using Google Map locally. 3. You can log in into our server and then request for your Call/SMS/location history and the server will send a GCM command and fetch the Call/SMS/locaiton history of your device. You can see your Call/SMS/location history from our website.  To be in compliance with Google Play Policy we will be showing notification in top bar whenever request for details is received and uploaded to website. Call/SMS/Location details will not be uploaded automatically it will be pulled only when user logs in to the website and request for pull. All information is stored securely in server in human unreadable format and the server and database is located in US. Users can optout any time and clear the details from server either through mobile or from website. The app cannot be used as spy app as the icon cannot be hidden and notifications cannot be disabled. com.zalebox.headboard.ideas.s1 () () () () () () (Headboard Ideas) () () () () () () () () (Choosing Quality Bedding For Comfort And Fashion) (     If you are considering redecorating your bedroom
column2: one of the easiest ways to add some extra flair and comfort without too many extra books is to simply invest in a new set of bedding.) (     Bedding fashions are right in step with other fashion trends
column3: and that means that floral patterns are out and solid color combinations are in. You should pick a color scheme that coordinates with your room color as well as the furniture in your bedroom. Also consider the other accessories in your bedroom such as paintings
column5: and mirrors before selecting bedding that will compliment the room and achieve the style and effect you are after.) (     Nothing beats a good duvet for looks or for style. You can buy duvet covers in many different styles
column6: and a duvet is a very comfortable replacement for the traditional quilt. Remember to buy both an inner and outer cover for your duvet
column7: and if you are allergy prone look into alternatives to the goose feather or down stuffed duvet. Watch out
column8: because testing by the Federal Food and Drug Agency has determined that no material is truly hypoallergenic
column9: as most materials could cause a negative reaction even if it's a minute portion of the population. Based on these findings
column10: the United States Supreme Court struck down the FDA's definition of hypoallergenic
column11: and thus there is no real standard for what the term actually means. Companies who manufacture duvets could technically market any product as hypoallergenic.) (     You will want to do your research on the company and how they approach their research before purchasing one of their “hypoallergenic” bedding products. Also
column12: keep in mind that materials such as cotton

column1: com.iforpowell.android.ipantman () () () () () () () () (IpSensorMan) () () (IpSensorMan 1.2.6) () () () (Welcome to this new version of IpSensorMan.  Recent changes:) (release: 1.2.6 date: 2012-05-20 - Fix for ANT failing to initialize after the ANT Radio Service  update 4.0 on slower phones with Bluetooth switched off. - Support for Polar and Zephyr standard Bluetooth HR sensors. - Not BTLE Still waiting on Google to make the necessary API's --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.5 date: 2012-03-24 - Adding support framework for BlueTooth Sensors. - Beta support for Zephyr and Polar initially. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.4 date: 2012-02-25 - Fix some issues with the new pedal smoothness and torque effectiveness power data fields. - Total rework of back end logging system. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.3 date: 2012-02-02 - More debug logging support especially for calibration. - Fixed bug with Slope setting. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.2 date: 2012-01-21 - More power calibration options where the device supports them. Auto Zero control
column2: Slope setting
column3: Crank length get and set. Improved debug logging. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.1 date: 2012-01-05 - Tweaks to the Temperature sensor code. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.0 date: 2012-12-30 - Added support for Foot pod and Temperature sensors.   - Support for the beta pedal smoothness and torque effectiveness power data fields. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.1.1 date: 2012-08-18 - Added low level debug logging option.  Added ability to manually add a sensor and set it's ID.  Will now detect the problematic Geonaute B'TWIN speed/cadence sensor.   --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.1.0 date: 2012-08-03 - Added support for opening multiple sensors of same type designated as yours.  This is to enable IpWatts. - Added support for pedaling percentage. - Fix intermittent bad cadence value from crank torque type sensor. - Prefer no data over bad high power data in very bad reception cases. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.0.3 date: 2012-07-27 - Optimizations after some work with profiling tools.  Reduced CPU usage and hopefully improved battery usage and runtime. - turned down the logging a bit more. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.0.2 date: 2012-07-13 - Improved ANT USB support
column5: - better error messaging. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.0.1 date: 2012-06-27 - Rebuild to support ANT USB sticks on USB HOST mode capable devices.  I consider this feature to be beta.  Feedback greatly appreciated
column6: please email me. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.0.0 date: 2012-06-09 - First full non beta release. - Removed logs and Device id capture in error reports and the permissions associated with this.  Turn logging right down. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.9.2 date: 2012-06-01 - more tweaking of the average cadence and power code. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.9.1 date: 2012-05-24 - Fix more cadence averaging fixes especially with bad ANT  reception conditions. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.9.0 date: 2012-05-16 - Fix Quark Cinqo cadence average issue. - Added in ANT+ branding. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.8.1 date: 2012-04-25 - Added ability to dump raw data and decode information to a file.  --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.8.0 date: 2012-04-12 - multiple application really working IpBike with IpPeloton - rework toggle bit decode to get passing certification tests --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.7.0 date: 2012-03-31 - Added calibration for Power sensors.  Fixed SRM bug. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.6.3 date: 2012-03-22 - special release with debug logging left on. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.6.2 date: 2012-02-27 - fix issue with dialog to get OiAbout app not showing - market button correctly. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.6.1 date: 2012-02-17 - Tweak analytics to get sensor count - Default automatic error reporting to on - tidy up searching

com.awabe.englishpronunciation () () () () () () () () () (English Pronunciation) () () () () () () () () () (Short vowels /ɪ/) (- The tongue is positioned forward and slightly lower in the oral cavity than for /i:/
column2: with the sides in contact with the teeth laterally and the tip positioned behind the lower teeth. - The mandible is slightly lower than for /i:/. - The lips are unrounded. - The vocal folds are adducted and vibrating. - The velopharyngeal port is closed.) () () () () () () () () () () () () (Short vowels /ʊ/) (- The tongue body is back and elevated into a mid-high position with contact against the upper molars
column3: while the tongue root is not as retracted as other back vowels. - The mandible is elevated but may lower slightly. - The lips are usually rounded and protruded. - The vocal folds are adducted and vibrating. - The velopharyngeal port is closed.) () () () () () () () () () () () () (Short vowels /ʌ/) (- Although variable
column4: the tongue is in the center of the oral cavity. - The jaw is slightly lowered
column5: although its position varies depending on phonetic context. - The lips are unrounded. - The vocal folds are adducted and vibrating. - The velopharyngeal port is closed.) () () () () () () () () () () () () (Short vowels /ɒ/) (- The tongue body is positioned back and low in the oral cavity. - The mandible is lowered more than the rest of the back vowels. - The lips are unrounded and wide open. - The vocal folds are adducted and vibrating. - The volopharygeal port is closed. ) () () () () () () () () () () () () (Short vowels /ə/) (- Although variable
column6: the tongue is slightly above the neutral position with some bunching in the palatal region. - The mandible is slightly lowered. - The lips are usually rounded. - The vocal folds are adducted and vibrating. - The velopharyngeal port is closed.) () () () () () () () () () () () () (Short vowels /e/) (- The tongue is positioned forward and high in the oral cavity with the sides in contact with the teeth laterally and the tip positioned behind the lower teeth. - The mandible is elevated. - The lips are unrounded
column7: and may be retracted. - The vocal folds are adducted and vibrating. - The velopharyngeal port is closed.) () () () () () () () () () () () () (Short vowels /æ/) (- The tongue is positioned slightly forward and low in the oral cavity
column8: with the tip positioned behind the lower teeth. - The mandible is lowered more than for any other front vowel. - The lips are unrounded but may be retracted. - The vocal folds are adducted and vibrating. - The velopharyngeal port is closed. ) () () () () () () () () ()

com.period.tracker.lite () () () () () () (TTC) () () () () (Predict Periods Using Luteal Length) () (Period Tracker normally predicts your next period start date using your average cycle length. For example
column2: if your average cycle length is 28 days
column3: Period Tracker will predict your next period as coming 28 days after the start of your last period.  Predict Periods Using luteal Length overrides this method of predicting of your next period once Period Tracker has detected that you've ovulated. Once ovulation is detected via the TTC notes that you've inputted
column4: instead of continuing to use your average cycle
column5: it will now predict your next period start date using your ovulation + luteal length. Your luteal length is the number of days that typically pass between your ovulation day and the start of your next period. Using this method once ovulation is detected will likely make your predicted period start date more accurate since luteal length for most women is fairly constant.  By default
column6: Period Tracker sets your luteal length as 14 days. However
column7: you can change your luteal length by going to your app's Settings/General/Ovulation page. Period Tracker will also change your luteal length to more accurately determine your luteal length by using your inputted TTC notes once you have inputted TTC notes for at least one cycle.)
